<subSubSection lastPageId="46" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,655,680]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species, like 
<emphasis box="[520,649,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName box="[520,645,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Neoephydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciligena">N. ciligena</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
has two basic color forms. The 
<typeStatus box="[1004,1102,655,680]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">holotype</typeStatus>
is a representative of the dark form, i.e., legs mostly microtomentose, grayish green to grayish blue. The second form is pale colored, i.e., legs at most thinly microtomentose, mostly yellowish to orangish. The conformation of the male terminalia of both forms is virtually identical.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399427/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" targetBox="[156,1432,872,1728]" targetPageId="45">
